---
By: Prentice Mulford
Locus:
  Page: 213
  Verse: 12
Tags:
  - Grief
---
To grieve at any loss, be it of friend or property, weakens mind and body.
It is no help to the friend grieved for. It is rather an injury; for our
sad thought must reach the person, even if passed to another condition of
existence, and is a source of pain to that person.
